Here is an example of a simple React component structure:


```
import React from 'react';

// Create the SimpleComponent class
class SimpleComponent extends React.Component {

  // Implement the render method
  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <h1>Simple React Component</h1>
        <p>This is a simple React component that renders a heading and a paragraph</p>
      </div>
    );
  }
}

export default SimpleComponent;
```

To use this `SimpleComponent`, you would need to import it into another file and add it to that file's JSX:

```
import React from 'react';
import SimpleComponent from './SimpleComponent';

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>My App</h2>
      <SimpleComponent />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

In this example, the `SimpleComponent` is imported and added to the `App` component's JSX. It would be rendered as part of the `App` component.
